The '''Vietnam Software Association''', known for short as '''VINASA''', is a software business association headquartered in Hanoi Software Centre, [[Hanoi]], [[Vietnam]]. It was established in 2002.<ref>{{cite news|work=Vietnam Express|url=http://vnexpress.net/Vietnam/Vi-tinh/2002/04/3B9BB89F/|date=2002-04-27|accessdate=2008-01-25|title=Hiệp hội Doanh nghiệp Phần mềm Việt Nam ra đời (Vietnam Software Association established)|last=Đoan|first=Trang|language=Vietnamese}}</ref> In 2005, they signed a cooperation agreement with the [[Japan External Trade Organization]] (JETRO).<ref>{{cite news|work=Vietnam Express|url=http://vnexpress.net/Vietnam/Vi-tinh/2005/09/3B9E21A3/|date=2005-09-15|accessdate=2008-01-25|title=VINASA và JETRO cùng thúc đẩy hợp tác CNTT (VINASA and JETRO conclude CNTT agreement)|last=Nguyễn|first=Hằng|language=Vietnamese}}</ref> Among other activities, they organise an annual software contest; in 2006, they gave out 36 prizes to various individuals and organisations.<ref>{{cite news|work=Việt Báo|url=http://vietbao.vn/Kinh-te/Vinasa-trao-36-giai-thuong-Sao-Khue-2006/45195721/87/|title=Vinasa trao 36 giải thưởng Sao Khuê 2006 (VINASA hands out 36 Sao Khuê prizes for 2006)|date=2006-05-27|accessdate=2008-01-25}}</ref>
